    "feat": {
        "name": "Cut them Down, Burn them Out",
        "type": "stat_block_section",
        "subtype": "feat",
        "text": "Inspired by the sixth line of the Crimson Oath, when you oppose the enemies of Lastwall, you aim to excise the rot from the land itself. Make a Strike against an undead creature using a weapon with which you have master proficiency. On a success, in addition to the attack\u2019s other effects, the creature takes a \u20132 status penalty to the DC of any curses, diseases, or poisons it can inflict for 1 round. On a critical success, the undead creature takes the \u20132 status penalty for 1 round, then a \u20131 status penalty for an additional round.",
        "level": 18,
